acceptance_tests:
EVERY historical .agent/qa/*.json validates against qa_verdict OR contract_review, with no edits: python3 -c "import json,glob,jsonschema,sys; qv=json.load(open('schema/qa_verdict.schema.json')); cr=json.load(open('schema/contract_review.schema.json')); bad=[]
for f in glob.glob('.agent/qa/*.json'):
    d=json.load(open(f))
    ok=False
    for s in (qv,cr):
        try: jsonschema.validate(d,s); ok=True; break
        except jsonschema.ValidationError: pass
    if not ok: bad.append(f)
sys.exit(1 if bad else 0)"

EVERY .agent/contracts/*.json validates against contract.schema.json: python3 -c "import json,glob,jsonschema,sys; s=json.load(open('schema/contract.schema.json')); bad=[f for f in glob.glob('.agent/contracts/*.json') if not _ok(f,s)] if False else []
import json as J
bad=[]
for f in glob.glob('.agent/contracts/*.json'):
